rComments: Professor MacDonald is great at teaching. He makes everything so straight-forward and easy to follow. He will answer any questions you have. Many of the examples he uses to teach are from past midterms and exams. He prepares you really well for those. The only reason I got a C is because I did the bare minimum. You can DEFINITELY get A+ if you try.

I loved prof MacDonald. He doesn't record his lectures and just does the lecture on whiteboard so it's over zoom, which means you really have to pay attention. THIS IS A GOOD THING. I'm doing better in this class than any of my others literally just because I am forced to pay attention for the entire class. He's really nice and he teaches well.

Prof Dan is great. You arent going to pass if you dont attend lectures, but if you follow the processes shown in class, the course really isnt that hard. He puts more emphasis on understanding the material than just memorizing equations, and your process is weighed much heavier than the math and resulting final answers. Awesome instructor

If you are a first-year who is not good at physics at all like me, well Prof. Macdonald teaches it like cake. I am the worst when solving physics, but Prof. Macdonald made every step of this course bearable. This course is not easy at all, but the way he teaches it makes sense. If you want an A+, take this course with Prof. Macdonald :)

He's a great professor but his grading is very tough. Cool guy but he doesn't give notes and this is a very hard subject. His lectures are excellent but the work outside of class is very hard and would be easier if he post his note. The out-of-class learning could be much better.

Professor Dan is awesome, he cares much more about us being able to problem solve than to do math, in his own words "this isn't a math course". He cares a lot about his students and does his best to get us ready for tests, although he doesn't make the tests easier. If you can make him fit in your schedule, ideal prof.
Funny guy. Makes learning enjoyable. Show up to the lectures and you'll be fine. :)

He does not post the notes online so you have to go to the lectures to get the material. His lectures are very good and he explains very well. The final was a little harder than the midterm but nothing too difficult. It's hard to find good engineering profs so I was lucky to have him.

The best professor I ever had, I had taken this course in the past but dropped it because it was too hard but Daniel makes the course look like a middle school physics course it is literally was so easy.

Professor Macdonald is amazing! Definitely take him if you can. He adapted to online learning quite well and uses a whiteboard which is easy to follow. He is also enthusiastic about what he teaches which actually made the class fun to attend. The midterm and final are pretty straightforward, they vary only a bit from what you do for homework.

Additive Manufacturing was a great introduction into the field. He explains really well as he is an expert and does his research on this stuff. Go to class and you wont have an issue. The material is easy to learn and really interesting. The project was fun and he makes it clear what his expectations are for the reports.
Gives clear expectations and good explanations. Go to class and youll pass.

This prof is a very good teacher and is clear on what he expects from students. Tells you what kind of questions are on the exam beforehand, which is really helpful for studying. Only difficulty is the problems in class are slightly easier than other problems. Other than that, he is very funny and keeps students interested! Highly recommend!

Overall he is a great Professor. His lectures are intresting, its one of the only classes where I don't struggle to stay awake. There are quizzes every week, but they aren't too difficult and they aren't worth much. You have to go to classes cause he doesn't post his notes online but the classes are worth it. I would recomend 10/10.

Daniel Macdonald is a real gem. He is really funny in class but also a great prof. There is one quiz every week but they aren't weighted too heavy. Wear goggles just in case he throws chalk at you when you talk in class. Great guy, great class, he should get a raise and teach me more classes.

Dan's a sick guy. Makes himself accessible to his students and is motivated to make sure every student knows what's going on. You HAVE to go to class as he doesn't post any slides. Overall a pretty chill class, easy to get an A if you put in work.

he is always willing to help his students. The class may seem hard but by going to lectures and watching videos, it's a piece of cake. Do all suggested problems he posts on the course website because they are great practice for what will be on ur evaluations. No trick questions on the exam as he will give you great hints with what to expect

he is a good and engaging prof who seems to genuinely know what it's like to be a student so he doesn't make texts mandatory though some other profs may. His lectures really feel more like a high school environment which is great for adapting to uni. Also, from my experience, he will remember you from the first day if you make an impression
Great professor. Weekly quizzes in the DGD. Highly recommend taking his course.
Very realistic and down to Earth guy. Says things how they are. Has a good sense of humour.
Super equals He is great at teaching and cares about the students
Great prof, take if you can

Dan is one of the greatest profs/TAs I've ever had. He's intelligent and charismatic, with a good sense of humor. An excellent lecturer. he does a great job of makings tough concepts easy to understand. Also very accommodating, go to office hours if you need help. He has a great future as eng prof at the university, and I wish him the best!

This manz took all the time and dedication to think about how he is gonna explain the course that he took as a student in a much clearer and interesting way. Fair exams and quizzes, and overall the most passionate prof in MCG. If only he taught thermo 2...

Love this man. Explains things clearly and simply, can sense when people are confused, gives good examples in class and good notes. He's probably one of the best engineering profs out there right now.

Dan is a really great professor and one of the few I can actually follow when he teaches. His notes are organized which is incredible. He makes a point to get to know his students and really wants everyone to succeed. Thermodynamics is a really tough course but he explains it in a way that makes sense. If you get the option take a class with him.

Dan is fantastic. Always happy, always trying to get the class evolved. I truly wish i could have taken him again in MCG1100. If he's doing GNG1105, he encourages just finding the textbook online, which theres also an pdf with all of the questions and answers from the manual. Personable guy, always looking out for us, and I wish him the best.

Dan is a great guy, sitting in the front row he always made an effort to make conversation before class. He is very clear with what is going to be tested and makes it easy to do well in his class while still learning. He is also quite fit, and that helps motivate me to go to lectures. If you want to see him outside of class hit up the gym.

Daniel is a great guy - really nice, approachable, and very knowledgeable. His pre-lab lectures are very concise and to the point and he is engaging to listen to. He also has a sense of humour so bring on the sass (especially when he "refuses" to give away answers.. if you're persistent, he will)

Had him for the dissection lab. Super cool guy, but he sometimes forgot that we are just first year students and don't know anything. He won't answer your questions (we had many), he just gives hints which can be frustrating. He had a great dynamic with our TA, and it made it fun to come to class every week. He is very nice and knows his stuff.
